and he started off by reading the Quran

00:32:39.930 --> 00:32:41.930
talaa alayhimul Quran

00:32:41.930 --> 00:32:42.930
according to the narration

00:32:42.930 --> 00:32:44.930
he got up and he read Quran to them

00:32:44.930 --> 00:32:46.930
and then the second thing he did

00:32:46.930 --> 00:32:47.930
he called them towards

00:32:47.930 --> 00:32:49.930
worshipping Allah alone

00:32:49.930 --> 00:32:50.930
these people were already Muslimin

00:32:50.930 --> 00:32:52.930
but he's inviting them again

00:32:52.930 --> 00:32:54.930
to tell them worship Allah alone

00:32:54.930 --> 00:32:55.930
reminding them

00:32:55.930 --> 00:32:59.930
and he got them interested in Islam

00:32:59.930 --> 00:33:01.930
and at the same time

00:33:01.930 --> 00:33:03.930
he then said

00:33:03.930 --> 00:33:05.930
there are two things

00:33:05.930 --> 00:33:07.930
two things that you need to bear witness

00:33:07.930 --> 00:33:08.930
or you need to pledge

00:33:08.930 --> 00:33:10.930
one is the pledge between you and Allah

00:33:10.930 --> 00:33:12.930
and one is the pledge between you and me

00:33:12.930 --> 00:33:14.930
what was the pledge between them and Allah?

00:33:14.930 --> 00:33:15.930
one thing

00:33:15.930 --> 00:33:17.930
worship Allah alone

00:33:17.930 --> 00:33:19.930
and don't engage in any form of shirk

00:33:19.930 --> 00:33:21.930
never ever associate a partner

00:33:21.930 --> 00:33:23.930
with Allah s.a.w.

00:33:23.930 --> 00:33:24.930
that was the pledge

00:33:24.930 --> 00:33:26.930
between them and Allah

00:33:26.930 --> 00:33:29.930
so this was the first part of the pledge

00:33:29.930 --> 00:33:31.930
I want to repeat it because it's important

00:33:31.930 --> 00:33:32.930
people don't like it sometimes

00:33:32.930 --> 00:33:34.930
when we speak of Tawheed, Tawheed

00:33:34.930 --> 00:33:35.930
and this is shirk and that is shirk

00:33:35.930 --> 00:33:38.930
wallahi anything where shirk is smelt

00:33:38.930 --> 00:33:40.930
we need to be far away from it

00:33:40.930 --> 00:33:41.930
if people are disputing something

00:33:41.930 --> 00:33:43.930
stay away

00:33:43.930 --> 00:33:44.930
we don't want it

00:33:44.930 --> 00:33:46.930
because it's better for us to do that

00:33:46.930 --> 00:33:47.930
which nobody is disputing

00:33:47.930 --> 00:33:49.930
there's enough in Islam

00:33:49.930 --> 00:33:51.930
of items that nobody disputes

00:33:51.930 --> 00:33:52.930
that we can engage in

00:33:52.930 --> 00:33:55.930
engage in before we enter into disputed territory

00:33:55.930 --> 00:33:58.930
may Allah s.a.w. protect us and grant us goodness

00:33:58.930 --> 00:34:00.930
so he said this is between you and Allah

00:34:00.930 --> 00:34:02.930
don't ever engage in shirk

00:34:02.930 --> 00:34:04.930
and between you and me

00:34:04.930 --> 00:34:08.210
he says, subhanallah

00:34:08.210 --> 00:34:10.210
I am pledging allegiance with you

00:34:10.210 --> 00:34:11.210
or you pledge with me

00:34:11.210 --> 00:34:14.210
that you will protect me from the same thing

00:34:14.210 --> 00:34:17.210
you protect your wives and your family members from

00:34:17.210 --> 00:34:18.210
anything that happens to them

00:34:18.210 --> 00:34:19.210
how do you protect them?

00:34:19.210 --> 00:34:21.210
that's how you will protect me

00:34:21.210 --> 00:34:22.210
and if you do that

00:34:22.210 --> 00:34:24.210
I will come in for Hijra

00:34:24.210 --> 00:34:26.210
and this was a beautiful statement

00:34:26.210 --> 00:34:29.210
because when people have their own children

00:34:29.210 --> 00:34:30.210
and their own wives

00:34:30.210 --> 00:34:32.210
how do they protect them?

00:34:32.210 --> 00:34:34.210
exactly how they would protect them

00:34:34.210 --> 00:34:36.210
he says, you consider me

00:34:36.210 --> 00:34:37.210
one of your own family

00:34:37.210 --> 00:34:39.210
and you would protect me

00:34:39.210 --> 00:34:42.210
so now they had heard this

00:34:42.210 --> 00:34:45.210
and Abu al-Haytham al-Tayyihan

00:34:45.210 --> 00:34:47.210
he was one of those who was there

00:34:47.210 --> 00:34:49.210
may Allah be pleased with them all

00:34:49.210 --> 00:34:51.210
he says, I have a question

00:34:51.210 --> 00:34:53.210
what's the question?

00:34:53.210 --> 00:34:55.210
say for example, you know we have the people

00:34:55.210 --> 00:34:57.210
we have signed treaties with and so on

00:34:57.210 --> 00:35:00.210
and one day if your deen

00:35:00.210 --> 00:35:03.210
if this deen of ours becomes so big and so on

00:35:03.210 --> 00:35:05.210
would you return to Makkat al-Mukarramah?

00:35:05.210 --> 00:35:06.210
would you return to Makkah?

00:35:06.210 --> 00:35:08.210
or would you consider yourselves

00:35:08.210 --> 00:35:10.210
yourself as one of us?

00:35:10.210 --> 00:35:12.210
so the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم says

00:35:12.210 --> 00:35:14.210
your treaties are mine

00:35:14.210 --> 00:35:17.210
I am from you and you are from me

00:35:17.210 --> 00:35:19.210
and Nabi صلى الله عليه وسلم made it very clear

00:35:19.210 --> 00:35:22.210
that once the Hijra takes place

00:35:22.210 --> 00:35:25.210
his new abode will be Al-Madinah

00:35:25.210 --> 00:35:27.210
so returning to Makkah

00:35:27.210 --> 00:35:29.210
would be out of a question

00:35:29.210 --> 00:35:30.210
and if you think of it carefully

00:35:30.210 --> 00:35:35.210
when the victory of Makkah happened

00:35:35.210 --> 00:35:38.210
Nabi صلى الله عليه وسلم did not stay in Makkah

00:35:38.210 --> 00:35:40.210
he returned to Madinah Munawwarah

00:35:40.210 --> 00:35:42.210
and he passed away there, Subhanallah

00:35:42.210 --> 00:35:43.210
look at this

00:35:43.210 --> 00:35:45.210
and this is why today

00:35:45.210 --> 00:35:47.210
you have Makkat al-Mukarramah

00:35:48.210 --> 00:35:52.210
the environment is so different

00:35:52.210 --> 00:35:54.210
in Makkah and in Madinah

00:35:54.210 --> 00:35:56.210
you feel Makkah, the heat, the mountains

00:35:56.210 --> 00:35:57.210
and so much

00:35:57.210 --> 00:36:00.210
and in Madinah you feel the calm, serene air

00:36:00.210 --> 00:36:01.210
you can feel it

00:36:01.210 --> 00:36:03.210
all those who visited it Masha'Allah

00:36:03.210 --> 00:36:04.210
you would know the difference

00:36:04.210 --> 00:36:07.210
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:36:07.210 --> 00:36:10.210
so upon that they pledged allegiance

00:36:10.210 --> 00:36:11.210
Subhanallah

00:36:11.210 --> 00:36:13.210
he said I will fight whom you fight

00:36:13.210 --> 00:36:15.210
and I make peace with whom you make peace with

00:36:15.210 --> 00:36:16.210
I am one of you

00:36:16.210 --> 00:36:17.210
they pledged allegiance

00:36:17.210 --> 00:36:21.210
and they were very very strong on that allegiance

00:36:21.210 --> 00:36:23.210
and the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم says

00:36:23.210 --> 00:36:26.210
let's select from amongst you 12 men

00:36:26.210 --> 00:36:28.210
just like Jesus may peace be upon him

00:36:28.210 --> 00:36:29.210
